# Dashboard (React)

Create React App + TypeScript. UI: React Bootstrap + styled-components. State: Redux Toolkit + RTK Query.

## Structure

```
pages/        Route-level views (HomePage, DashboardPage, admin/*)
components/   Reusable UI (common/, subscriptions/, dashboard/, layout/)
constants/    Shared config (e.g. serverNav.ts for dashboard server shell)
store/        Redux slices + RTK Query API modules (store/api/)
types/        Shared interfaces (ISettings, IServer, User, â€¦)
helpers/      Hooks, theme, Discord/Stripe utilities
```

## Server dashboard layout

Server-scoped routes (`/dashboard/:serverId/*`) use a shared shell:

- [`constants/serverNav.ts`](dashboard/src/constants/serverNav.ts) â€” grouped nav sections, item metadata (path, name, icon, description), and `getServerNavItem()`
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx) â€” sidebar + page header + outlet wrapper
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerPageHeader.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerPageHeader.tsx) â€” page title row with nav icon, premium badge, and mobile menu button
- Desktop: sticky grouped sidebar; mobile: Offcanvas nav from header menu button
- Layout/nav tokens live in [`helpers/theme.ts`](dashboard/src/helpers/theme.ts) (`layout`, `nav`, `layout.padding`, `layout.breakpoints`)

